the analytical framework for policy design regarding public safety in Japan.\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003eThe professer has been working for the National Police Agency (NPA) for twenty-five years and she will be at SFC until March 2022.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp style=\"color: #856a5d;\"\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003ch4 style=\"background-color: #ccecff; padding-left: 8px; font-weight: bold;\"\u003e教材・参考文献\u003c/h4\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eWhite paper on police\u003cbr\u003eWhite paper on crime\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003ch4 style=\"background-color: #ccecff; padding-left: 8px; font-weight: bold;\"\u003e提出課題・試験・成績評価の方法など\u003c/h4\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eStudents will be graded based on class attendance, assignments and final report.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp style=\"color: #856a5d;\"\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003ch4 style=\"background-color: #ccecff; padding-left: 8px; font-weight: bold;\"\u003e履修上の注意\u003c/h4\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eThis syllabus is tentative and is likely to change.  Especially special lectures by guest speakers are yet to be confirmed.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp style=\"color: #856a5d;\"\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\n\u003ch4 style=\"background-color: #ccecff; padding-left: 8px; font-weight: bold;\"\u003e授業計画\u003c/h4\u003e\n  \u003cp\u003e\n  \u003cu\u003e第1回 Introduction\u003c/u\u003e\n  \u003c/p\u003e\n  \u003cp\u003e\n  \u003c/p\u003e\u003cp\u003eI will explain the scheduled plan and the grading policy.\u003cbr\u003eI will talk about the data on public safety in Japan as introduction to this course.\u003c/p\u003e\n  \u003cp style=\"color: #856a5d;\"\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n  \n  \u003cp\u003e  \u003c/p\u003e\n  \u003chr\u003e\n  \u003cp\u003e\n  \u003cu\u003e第2回 Police law (1)\u003c/u\u003e\n  \u003c/p\u003e\n  \u003cp\u003e\n  \u003c/p\u003e\u003cp\u003eBasic knowledge of police law in Japan. Police history, current police system and police organization.\u003c/p\u003e\n  \u003cp style=\"color: #856a5d;\"\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n  \n  \u003cp\u003e  \u003c/p\u003e\n  \u003chr\u003e\n  \u003cp\u003e\n  \u003cu\u003e第3回 Police law (2)\u003c/u\u003e\n  \u003c/p\u003e\n  \u003cp\u003e\n  \u003c/p\u003e\u003cp\u003eHuman resources, budget of Japan police, and theory on limitation of police power.\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n  \u003cp style=\"color: #856a5d;\"\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n  \n  \u003cp\u003e  \u003c/p\u003e\n  \u003chr\u003e\n  \u003cp\u003e\n  \u003cu\u003e第4回 Police law (3)\u003c/u\u003e\n  \u003c/p\u003e\n  \u003cp\u003e\n  \u003c/p\u003e\u003cp\u003eThe police reforms and their influence.\u003cbr\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n  \u003cp style=\"color: #856a5d;\"\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n  \n  \u003cp\u003e  \u003c/p\u003e\n  \u003chr\u003e\n  \u003cp\u003e\n  \u003cu\u003e第5回 Special lecture \"Intelligence\"\u003c/u\u003e\n  \u003c/p\u003e\n  \u003cp\u003e\n  \u003c/p\u003e\u003cp\u003eMr. Yoshiki Kobayashi, professor at Meiji University, former Councilor and senior analyst of the Cabinet Intelligence and Research Office, gives a special lecture on \"Intelligence.\" He was a professor at SFC from April 2010 to March 2013.\u003c/p\u003e\n  \u003cp style=\"color: #856a5d;\"\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n  \n  \u003cp\u003e  \u003c/p\u003e\n  \u003chr\u003e\n  \u003cp\u003e\n  \u003cu\u003e第6回 Criminal procedure\u003c/u\u003e\n  \u003c/p\u003e\n  \u003cp\u003e\n  \u003c/p\u003e\u003cp\u003eBasic knowledge of criminal procedure.\u003c/p\u003e\n  \u003cp style=\"color: #856a5d;\"\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n  \n  \u003cp\u003e  \u003c/p\u003e\n  \u003chr\u003e\n  \u003cp\u003e\n  \u003cu\u003e第7回 Special lecture \" International terrorism\"\u003c/u\u003e\n  \u003c/p\u003e\n  \u003cp\u003e\n  \u003c/p\u003e\u003cp\u003eThe senior officer of the National Police Agency gives a special lecture on \"International terrorism.\" \u003c/p\u003e\n  \u003cp style=\"color: #856a5d;\"\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n  \n  \u003cp\u003e  \u003c/p\u003e\n  \u003chr\u003e\n  \u003cp\u003e\n  \u003cu\u003e第8回 Comprehensive approach to crime prevention \u003c/u\u003e\n  \u003c/p\u003e\n  \u003cp\u003e\n  \u003c/p\u003e\u003cp\u003eThe comprehensive approach to crime prevention.\u003cbr\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n  \u003cp style=\"color: #856a5d;\"\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n  \n  \u003cp\u003e  \u003c/p\u003e\n  \u003chr\u003e\n  \u003cp\u003e\n  \u003cu\u003e第9回 Recent criminal legislation amendments\u003c/u\u003e\n  \u003c/p\u003e\n  \u003cp\u003e\n  \u003c/p\u003e\u003cp\u003eThe recent amendments to the Penal Code regarding sexual offences.\u003c/p\u003e\n  \u003cp style=\"color: #856a5d;\"\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n  \n  \u003cp\u003e  \u003c/p\u003e\n  \u003chr\u003e\n  \u003cp\u003e\n  \u003cu\u003e第10回 Special lecture \"Cyber security\"\u003c/u\u003e\n  \u003c/p\u003e\n  \u003cp\u003e\n  \u003c/p\u003e\u003cp\u003eMr. Noboru Nakatani, an executive officer of Yahoo Japan, former executive director of the IGCI, Interpol Global Complex for Innovation in Singapore, gives a special lecture on cybersecurity.\u003c/p\u003e\n  \u003cp style=\"color: #856a5d;\"\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n  \n  \u003cp\u003e  \u003c/p\u003e\n  \u003chr\u003e\n  \u003cp\u003e\n  \u003cu\u003e第11回 Special lecture \"Cybercrime situation\"\u003c/u\u003e\n  \u003c/p\u003e\n  \u003cp\u003e\n  \u003c/p\u003e\u003cp\u003eMr, Takashi Sato, the director of the cybercrime technology division of the National Police Agency gives a special lecture on cybercrime situations in Japan.\u003c/p\u003e\n  \u003cp style=\"color: #856a5d;\"\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n  \n  \u003cp\u003e  \u003c/p\u003e\n  \u003chr\u003e\n  \u003cp\u003e\n  \u003cu\u003e第12回 Current issue of public safety\u003c/u\u003e\n  \u003c/p\u003e\n  \u003cp\u003e\n  \u003c/p\u003e\u003cp\u003eOverview of some theme regarding current issue of public safety.\u003c/p\u003e\n  \u003cp style=\"color: #856a5d;\"\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n  \n  \u003cp\u003e  \u003c/p\u003e\n  \u003chr\u003e\n  \u003cp\u003e\n  \u003cu\u003e第13回 Current situation of police investigation\u003c/u\u003e\n  \u003c/p\u003e\n  \u003cp\u003e\n  \u003c/p\u003e\u003cp\u003eThe situation surrounding police investigations.\u003c/p\u003e\n  \u003cp style=\"color: #856a5d;\"\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n  \n  \u003cp\u003e  \u003c/p\u003e\n  \u003chr\u003e\n  \u003cp\u003e\n  \u003cu\u003e第14回 Review\u003c/u\u003e\n  \u003c/p\u003e\n  \u003cp\u003e\n  \u003c/p\u003e\u003cp\u003eReview\u003c/p\u003e\n  \u003cp style=\"color: #856a5d;\"\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n  \n  \u003cp\u003e  \u003c/p\u003e\n  \u003chr\u003e\n  \u003cp\u003e\n  \u003cu\u003e第15回 Final report\u003c/u\u003e\n  \u003c/p\u003e\n  \u003cp\u003e\n  \u003c/p\u003e\u003cp\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n  \u003cp style=\"color: #856a5d;\"\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n  \n  \u003cp\u003e  \u003c/p\u003e\n  \u003chr\u003e\n\n  \u003cu\u003e15回目に相当するその他の授業計画\u003c/u\u003e\u003cbr\u003e\n  \u003cp\u003eassignments, report\u003c/p\u003e\n  \u003cp style=\"color: #856a5d;\"\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n","course_code":"政策立案論","default_view":"modules","root_account_id":1,"enrollment_term_id":3,"license":null,"grade_passback_setting":null,"end_at":null,"public_syllabus":false,"public_syllabus_to_auth":true,"storage_quota_mb":30000,"is_public_to_auth_users":true,"term":{"id":3,"name":"2020年秋学期","start_at":null,"end_at":null,"created_at":"2020-09-03T21:25:41Z","workflow_state":"active","grading_period_group_id":null},"apply_assignment_group_weights":false,"calendar":{"ics":"https://sol.sfc.keio.ac.jp/feeds/calendars/course_Utk30f1GQDjCPxIZGF5yRUI6fgWe6iYY6cnp2Xkx.ics"},"time_zone":"Asia/Tokyo","blueprint":false,"enrollments":[],"hide_final_grades":false,"workflow_state":"available","restrict_enrollments_to_course_dates":false,"overridden_course_visibility":""}